Url.Title: Using the Instrument Log
Url.Abstract: Using the Instrument Log The Instrument Log displays the current list of instrument messages along with the log time (date and time), run, category, and a brief description of what occurred. The entries displayed in this log include: instrument errors, run status (e.g., starting stopping, and rejecting runs), calibration (when new calibration results are saved), data file acceptor (path and filename of stored data), Autosampler (loading and unloading of pans), miscellaneous and power supply messages, taring (which TGA pan(s) are tared and its offset).

Url.Title: Configuring the Instrument Log
Url.Abstract: Configuring the Instrument Log To sort the instrument messages for display in the instrument log, check those that will be displayed and leave those that you do not wish to be displayed blank. You can choose to sort the messages by the categories displayed or by the severity of the message.

Url.Abstract: Clearing the Instrument Log You can selectively clear off the instrument messages, if desired, using this window. You can select the Keep the Last button then choose the Month(s) and Week(s) that you wish to leave in the log.

The run will automatically start when the flange, which is part of the cell structure, has reached the correct temperature. No action is required. For LNCS the flange must reach -160C with liquid detected for the run to proceed automatically.

Url.Title: Message 678

The Datafile Acceptor (DFA) is not communicating to send the data from the instrument to the controller. The sequence is halted so that the problem can be corrected without overwriting the data file.

The data file was transferred to the destination, but it was unable to confirm the file disposition.

The communication between the instrument and the DFA were interrupted. the problem could also be that the data file path name specified on the controller Experiment View is not valid or no longer exists.

Url.Title: Message 681

The communication was never established at the start of the run, so the specified destination of the DFA is not responding.

In addition, this error can occur falsely after loading instrument software or resetting instrument parameters. This message lists the impedance value that triggered the error as well as the range that the value fell outside.

Url.Title: Message 651
Url.Abstract: Message 651 Flow rate for selected gas cannot be controlled. Problem: The mass flow rate method segment was selected while the selected gas is "outside purge." When the outside purge is specified the flow rate is not controlled by the MFC, it is controlled by an external flow meter.

Url.Title: Message 652
Url.Abstract: Message 652 Run cannot start - specified flow rate cannot be reached. Problem: There is a problem with the gas supply. The flow rate specified on the Notes page for the current run cannot be attained.

Url.Title: Message 653
Url.Abstract: Message 653 Gas switching not allowed in a method when "none" is a selected gas type. Problem: You have selected a run segment that will cause the instrument to switch to a different gas at some point in the experiment, but you have selected "none" as the gas for that port.

Url.Title: Message 654

Url.Title: Message 655
Url.Abstract: Message 655 Run terminated - specified flow rate cannot be maintained. There is a problem with the gas supply. The specified flow rate needed for the balance cannot be maintained for the duration of the run. The run has stopped because the option, "Stop experiment when flow rate deviates from the set value" was selected on the Instrument Preferences MFC Purge Page.

Url.Title: Message 656
Url.Abstract: Message 656 Sample purge gas cannot reach specified flow rate. Problem: There is a problem with the gas supply. The flow rate specified for the current run cannot be attained.

Url.Title: Message 657

Url.Title: Message 658
Url.Abstract: Message 658 Gas switching is not allowed when gas 1 is outside purge. Problem: You have set Gas 1 to be an "outside purge," this means that the flow cannot be regulated through the instrument. You cannot include a switch gas segment in your method because it requires a designated flow rate.

Url.Title: Message 659
Url.Abstract: Message 659 Cannot select gas as "none" when "outside purge" is other selected gas. Problem: You have set one gas to be an "outside purge," this means that the flow cannot be regulated through the instrument using the Mass Flow Controller (MFC). An external flow meter is required. Therefore you cannot select the other gas to be "none" for the TGA because the gas flow rate to the balance and sample area must be individually regulated.

Url.Title: Message 660
Url.Abstract: Message 660 Cannot switch to a gas selected as "none." You have selected a run segment that will cause the instrument to switch to a different gas at some point in the experiment, but you have selected "none" as the gas for that port.

Url.Title: Message 661
Url.Abstract: Message 661 Flow measurement stopped, run terminated. There is a problem with the system. (The mass flow is not responding.)

Url.Title: Message 662
Url.Abstract: Message 662 Flow segment not allowed when mass flow controller is not installed. Problem: The flow segment depends on the presence of the Mass Flow Controller (MFC) in order to regulate the gas flow. If the MFC is not installed, the flow segment cannot be used.

Url.Title: Message 663
Url.Abstract: Message 663 Gas switching method segment not allowed when gas 1 is outside purge. You have set Gas 1 to be an "outside purge," this means that the flow cannot be regulated through the instrument. You cannot include a switch gas segment in your method because it requires a designated flow rate.

Url.Title: Message 664
Url.Abstract: Message 664 Must change the sample gas to gas 2 before selecting gas 1 as outside purge. Problem: The gas flow rate to the sample (furnace) and balance must be individually controlled. This can not be achieved when both the sample and balance are Gas #1 and Gas #1 is "outside purge." Outside purge requires that the flow rate be controlled externally from the instrument, therefore the sample and balance gas cannot be both Gas #1 (as specified on the Notes page).

Url.Title: Message 666

Url.Title: Message 173

Url.Title: Message 233
Url.Abstract: Message 233 Nitrogen is recommended for air bearing gas over 400°C. Problem: You have programmed a temperature over 400°C, but have not selected nitrogen for the air bearing gas.

Url.Title: Message 234
Url.Abstract: Message 234 Clamp size does not match sample size. Cannot start run. Problem: The sample length entered differs more than 1 mm from the current clamp calibration.

Url.Title: Message 235
Url.Abstract: Message 235 Perform clamp compliance calibration before proceeding. Problem: You have selected or installed the 3-point bending, compression, or submersion compression clamp, but you have not calibrated or recalibrated the clamp compliance.

Url.Title: Message 250
Url.Abstract: Message 250 Analog board failed confidence test. Cannot start or measure. Problem: The analog board did not pass the confidence test.

Url.Title: Message 251

Url.Title: Message 252

Url.Title: Message 253
Url.Abstract: Message 253 Instrument still warming up. Cannot start, move, or measure. Problem: You have attempted to begin using the instrument before it has fully warmed up.

Url.Title: Message 254
Url.Abstract: Message 254 Air bearing gas pressure too low. Cannot start, move or measure. Problem: The instrument must be operated with the appropriate air bearing gas pressure.

Url.Title: Message 255
Url.Abstract: Message 255 Instrument position not calibrated. Cannot start or measure. Problem: You have not calibrated the instrument's position or the calibration has been lost.

Url.Title: Message 256
Url.Abstract: Message 256 Clamp not supported in current mode. Cannot start or measure. Problem: The selected clamp is not appropriate for the current instrument mode (i.e., a penetration clamp used for the DMA Multi-frequency mode).

Url.Title: Message 257
Url.Abstract: Message 257 Clamp not calibrated. Cannot start or measure. Problem: The clamp that is currently installed on the instrument has not been calibrated.

Url.Title: Message 258
Url.Abstract: Message 258 Amplitude table empty. Cannot start or measure. Problem: The amplitude table that you have attempted to use has no amplitude values contained in it.

Url.Title: Message 259
Url.Abstract: Message 259 Cannot change amplitude table for active run. Problem: You have changed the amplitude table while the run was in progress.

Url.Title: Message 260
Url.Abstract: Message 260 Calibration in progress. Cannot start, move or measure. Problem: The instrument is currently busy performing calibration functions and cannot start another function at this time.

Url.Title: Message 261
Url.Abstract: Message 261 Method running. Cannot zero clamp, measure, or move clamp. Problem: An experiment is already in progress on the instrument. You cannot perform any functions that will move the clamp (such as zeroing or measuring) while the method is running.

Url.Title: Message 262
Url.Abstract: Message 262 Instrument not calibrated. Cannot start or measure. Problem: The force, electronic, or dynamic calibration has not been performed or has been lost.

Url.Title: Message 263
Url.Abstract: Message 263 Frequency sweep segment not valid in current mode. Cannot start run. Problem: The frequency sweep segment will not work with the instrument in its current mode (frequency scan is not applicable).

Url.Title: Message 264
Url.Abstract: Message 264 Strain sweep segment not valid in current mode. Cannot start run. Problem: The strain sweep segment will not work with the instrument in its current mode (strain is not applicable).

Url.Title: Message 265
Url.Abstract: Message 265 Displace segment not valid in current mode. Cannot start run. Problem: The Displacement time segment will not work with the instrument in its current mode (displacement is not applicable).

Url.Title: Message 266
Url.Abstract: Message 266 Force segments not valid in current mode. Cannot start run. Problem: The force segments will not work with the instrument in its current mode (force is not applicable).

Url.Title: Message 267
Url.Abstract: Message 267 Isostrain segment not valid in current mode. Cannot start run. Problem: The isostrain segment will not work with the instrument in its current mode (isostrain is not applicable).

Url.Title: Message 268
Url.Abstract: Message 268 Calibration in progress. Cannot move furnace. Problem: You cannot move the furnace while calibration is in progress.

Url.Title: Message 270
Url.Abstract: Message 270 Drive board not responding. Measurement terminated. Problem: A problem exists with the digital signal processor on the drive board. Measurement and method terminated.

Url.Title: Message 271
Url.Abstract: Message 271 Furnace opened while method running. Run terminated. Problem: You have manually opened the furnace while an experiment was running. The instrument has stopped the run.

Url.Title: Message 272
Url.Abstract: Message 272 Air bearing gas pressure too low. Drive stopped. Problem: The pressure of the air bearing gas is too low for the instrument to operate. The drive has been stopped.

Url.Title: Message 273
Url.Abstract: Message 273 Air bearing gas pressure too low. Drive stopped and run terminated. Problem: The pressure of the air bearing gas is too low for the instrument to operate. The drive has been stopped and the experiment terminated.

Url.Title: Message 274
Url.Abstract: Message 274 Position calibration lost. Problem: The instrument was turned off, reset, or experienced a power failure while the drive was active and the old position calibration is no longer valid.

Url.Title: Message 275
Url.Abstract: Message 275 GCA filled too full. Automatically reducing liquid to a safe level. Problem: During the manual filling process, the GCA was filled with too much liquid nitrogen.

Url.Title: Message 276
Url.Abstract: Message 276 GCA too full. Run will start when liquid is reduced to a safe level. Problem: This message occurs if you attempt to start a method while the GCA is in the process of boiling off excess liquid nitrogen. See message 275 .

Url.Title: Message 277
Url.Abstract: Message 277 GCA pressure is too high. Gas flow is blocked. Run terminated. Problem: While you were running a method, the pressure rose to 8 pounds or more. The gas flow is blocked.

Url.Title: Message 278
Url.Abstract: Message 278 Furnace position sensor error. Cannot move furnace or run. Problem: Both the furnace open and closed sensors are active at the same time. The sensor may be faulty.

Url.Title: Message 279
Url.Abstract: Message 279 GCA tank empty. Method continuing without GCA cooling. Problem: The storage tank on the GCA has run out of liquid nitrogen.

Url.Title: Message 280
Url.Abstract: Message 280 Liquid nitrogen bulk storage tank empty. Problem: This message can only occur when using the GCA Autofill option. The large bulk storage tank has run out of liquid nitrogen.

Url.Title: Message 281
Url.Abstract: Message 281 GCA liquid level sensor error. Problem: The liquid nitrogen level sensor in the GCA is faulty.

Url.Title: Message 283
Url.Abstract: Message 283 Furnace open at method start. Temperature control will be inactive. Problem: The furnace was left open during the start of a method. The instrument will not control the temperature during the experiment.

Url.Title: Message 284
Url.Abstract: Message 284 Sample geometry not valid for current clamp. Select new geometry. Problem: The sample geometry currently selected in the software is not valid for the clamp that is installed on the instrument.

Url.Title: Message 285
Url.Abstract: Message 285 Slide reached ____ mm. Sample yielded. Run terminated. Problem: The sample has yielded, broken, or melted causing the drive shaft to reach the end of its limit (~25 mm travel). This will automatically end the experiment.

Url.Title: Message 286
Url.Abstract: Message 286 Submersion clamp: Cannot close furnace. Problem: You have attempted to close the furnace. This cannot be done with the submersion clamp installed.

Url.Title: Message 287
Url.Abstract: Message 287 Sample size or geometry unusable for stress/force control. Cannot start run. Problem: This error message is displayed if you try to run in Multifrequency Controlled Stress mode without selecting a geometry and setting sample dimensions. The run will not be started.

Url.Title: Message 288
Url.Abstract: Message 288 Oscillation amplitude is zero. Check size and strain level. Problem: When performing DMA experiments, you can specify oscillation amplitude on the Procedure Page as either displacement (µm) or strain (%) for the Multifrequency Strain and Multistrain modes.

Url.Title: Message 289
Url.Abstract: Message 289 Stress table empty. Cannot start or measure. Problem: There are no entries in the stress table. The experiment cannot start and the sample cannot be measured.

Url.Title: Message 290
Url.Abstract: Message 290 Force table empty. Cannot start or measure. There are no entries in the force table. The experiment cannot start and the sample cannot be measured.

Url.Title: Status Message 291
Url.Abstract: Status Message 291 Strain or displacement ramp ended by static force limit. This is a status message to let you know that the drive force being applied has reached its limit, which resulted in the termination of the displacement or strain ramp. There are three possible reasons for termination of strain and displacement ramps:

Url.Title: Message 300
Url.Abstract: Message 300 Position not calibrated. Problem: The position of the drive shaft and slide must be calibrated in order for the optical encoder to accurately read the movement of the clamp. The position calibration has not been performed or has been lost.

Url.Title: Message 301
Url.Abstract: Message 301 Bad interface or drive board. Cannot calibrate. Problem: The interface or drive board has failed.

Url.Title: Message 302
Url.Abstract: Message 302 Method active. Cannot start calibration. Problem: An experiment is already in progress on the instrument. You cannot perform any calibration functions while the experiment is running.

Url.Title: Message 303
Url.Abstract: Message 303 Previous step or calibration not done. Problem: When performing the calibration, the steps must be followed in sequence for proper calibration of the instrument.

Url.Title: Message 306
Url.Abstract: Message 306 Calculated gain and/or offset is too small. Problem: The force gain and/or offset calculated are outside of the acceptable range.

Url.Title: Message 307
Url.Abstract: Message 307 Calculated gain and/or offset is too large. Problem: There is a problem with the DMA thermocouple calibration circuit.

Url.Title: Message 308
Url.Abstract: Message 308 Furnace open. Calibration proceeding. Close furnace for best results. Problem: The furnace was either not closed or was closing when a calibration was started.

Url.Title: Message 309
Url.Abstract: Message 309 Calibration already in progress. Cannot start new calibration. Problem: You cannot calibrate the instrument while it is already in the process of performing a calibration.

Url.Title: Message 311
Url.Abstract: Message 311 Force for full slide travel is too large. Problem: This message can occur during calibration if too much force is required to move the drive shaft (slide) to the top of its range. The cause may be one of the following:

Url.Title: Message 312
Url.Abstract: Message 312 Force for full slide travel is too small. Problem: This message can occur during calibration if the drive shaft does not move smoothly during the force calibration. The cause may be one of the following:

Url.Title: Message 313
Url.Abstract: Message 313 Range of slide or clamp travel is too small. Problem: This message can occur during calibration if there is less than 20 mm of travel range for the drive shaft (slide). (The full drive shaft travel range is 25 mm from top to bottom.) The cause may be one of the following:

Url.Title: Message 314
Url.Abstract: Message 314 Could not move the slide. Problem: This message can occur during calibration if the drive shaft does not move. The cause may be one of the following:

Url.Title: Message 315
Url.Abstract: Message 315 Sample is too stiff. Problem: This message can occur during dynamic calibration if the sample is too thick. Use a steel sample that is between 0.12 mm (0.005 inch) and 2.0 mm (0.08 inch) thick.

Url.Title: Message 316
Url.Abstract: Message 316 Sample is too weak. Problem: This message can occur during dynamic calibration if the sample is too thin and weak. Use a steel sample that is between 0.12 mm (0.005 inch) and 2.0 mm (0.08 inch) thick.

Url.Title: Message 317
Url.Abstract: Message 317 Clamp hit top of furnace. Remove clamp and repeat calibration. Problem: This message can occur if you did not remove the fixed and moveable clamps before dynamic calibration.

Url.Title: Message 318
Url.Abstract: Message 318 Negative compliance. Check sample dimensions and modulus. Problem: This message can occur during compliance calibration, if the sample dimension has been incorrectly entered.

Url.Title: Message 319
Url.Abstract: Message 319 Run memory full. Restart with the compliance sample. Problem: This message can occur during dynamic calibration, if you run more than 10 samples to gather your dynamic compliance data.

Url.Title: Message 320
Url.Abstract: Message 320 Bad dynamic calibration results. Results not saved. Problem: The lowest compliance, or thinnest sample, used in the dynamic calibration procedure was too weak. Use a steel sample that is between 0.12 mm (0.005 inch) and 2.0 mm (0.08 inch) thick.

Url.Title: Message 321
Url.Abstract: Message 321 Wrong clamp type. Use the dual cantilever clamp. Problem: The clamp used in the dynamic calibration procedure must be the dual cantilever

Url.Title: Message 322
Url.Abstract: Message 322 Position calibration has been corrupted. Recalibrate position. Problem: The position of the drive shaft and slide must be calibrated in order for the optical encoder to accurately read the movement of the clamp. The position calibration has been corrupted or lost.

Url.Title: Message 323
Url.Abstract: Message 323 Position versus force anomaly detected. Repeat calibration. Problem: This message can occur as a result of the drive shaft binding or a force spike occurring, during a position, mass, or force calibration.

Url.Title: Message 324
Url.Abstract: Message 324 Low air pressure or cold frame. Problem: The instrument may not be warmed up enough or there could be a problem with the air supply to the instrument.

Url.Title: Message 325
Url.Abstract: Message 325 Zero sample size. Enter sample dimensions. You must enter the dimension of the compliance sample when it is used during dynamic calibration. This message is posted if any dimension (length, width, thickness) is zero at this step.

Url.Title: Status Message 641

Url.Title: Message 824

Url.Title: Message 827
Url.Abstract: Message 827 Force calibration stored. This is an informational message to let you know that the force calibration recently performed has been stored for use with the instrument.

Url.Abstract: Message 828 Electronics calibration stored. Clamp calibration cleared. This message is to alert you that the electronics calibration just performed has been successfully stored. This automatically clears the existing clamp calibration. You must now calibrate the installed clamp.

Url.Title: Message 829
Url.Abstract: Message 829 Dynamic calibration stored. This is an informational message to let you know that the dynamic calibration recently performed has been stored for use with the instrument.

Url.Title: Message 830
Url.Abstract: Message 830 Position calibrated. This status message lets you know that the DMA has been calibrated for clamp position.

Url.Title: Message 858
Url.Abstract: Message 858 Calibration aborted. Problem: You have pressed the STOP key on the touch screen while the instrument was performing a calibration step. The calibration is cancelled.

Url.Title: Message 859
Url.Abstract: Message 859 Filling cooling unit. The cooling accessory is currently filling with liquid nitrogen. Please wait until the operation has been completed before continuing.

Url.Title: Message 860
Url.Abstract: Message 860 Creep stress exceeds available force. Problem: You have entered a stress for this creep mode experiment that requires more drive force than the DMA can provide.

Url.Title: Message 861
Url.Abstract: Message 861 Submersion clamps for use with aqueous or buffer solutions below 80°C only. Problem: You cannot use the submersion compression or submersion film/fiber clamps with aqueous solutions above 80°C. The clamps are primarily designed to evaluate polymeric materials in aqueous or buffer solutions over the temperature range -50°C (but above freezing point) to 80°C. Because of the volume of fluid (and its associated heat capacity), these submersion measurements are usually performed under isothermal conditions ramping at 2°C/min or less. The clamps are designed for aqueous or buffer solutions and should not be used with fluids whose vapor pressure results in volatility at the temperature of usage.

Url.Title: Status Message 864
Url.Abstract: Status Message 864 Force calibration complete. Please remove the 50g mass from the tray. The instrument has finished calibrating the force using the 50 gram mass. Please remove the mass from the tray before proceeding.

Url.Title: Message 920
Url.Abstract: Message 920 Poisson's Ratio set This is an informational message to let you know that Poisson's ratio has been set at the value displayed. This is the DMA parameter that defines the ratio of transverse contraction per unit dimension to the elongation per unit length, when the sample is subjected to a tensile stress. Typical values are: 0.5 for rubber materials, 0.33 for metals, and 0.44 for most plastics. Consult a chemistry reference book such as the CRC Handbook of Chemistry and Physics for applicable values.

Url.Title: Message 1030
Url.Abstract: Message 1030 GCA tank empty. Cannot start GCA autodiagnostic routine. Problem: The GCA tank must be filled with liquid nitrogen before it can be used for cooling experiments with the DMA, and it has registered as empty. The Autodiagnostic routine cannot be run until it is full.

Url.Title: DSC Messages
Url.Abstract: DSC Messages These messages can apply to the any of the TA Instruments' Differential Scanning Calorimeter instruments online with the controller. Refer to the Help messages for solutions to the problems.

Url.Title: Message 147
Url.Abstract: Message 147 Cell temperature will not equilibrate. Run terminated. Problem: The run has stopped and data has been saved. The cell could not reach the desired temperature within 90 minutes from the start of an Initial, Equilibrate, or Increment segment. Either the cell temperature is more than 4.0°C from the set point or the cell temperature is changing by more than 0.50°C/min.

Url.Title: Message 149
Url.Abstract: Message 149 Cell upper pressure limit exceeded. Run terminated. Problem: While a Pressure DSC cell experiment was running, the pressure in the cell reached and surpassed the upper limit allowed. The experiment has been stopped.

Url.Title: Message 151
Url.Abstract: Message 151 Air cool segment not valid for current cell. Cannot start run. Problem: You have tried to select the air cool segment with a cell that cannot use the air cool segment.

Url.Title: Message 152
Url.Abstract: Message 152 LNCS segment not valid in current mode. Cannot start run. Problem: The mode or instrument that you are attempting to use cannot work with the LNCS. The DSC Q10 is not compatible with the LNCS.

Url.Title: Message 153

Url.Title: Message 154
Url.Abstract: Message 154 Cell not responding. Could not save data in cell memory. Problem: This message is caused by one of the following:

Url.Title: Message 156
Url.Abstract: Message 156 Unknown cell type. Cannot run cell. Problem: The instrument does not recognize the cell connected to it, and therefore cannot start.

Url.Title: Message 158
Url.Abstract: Message 158 Cell not installed or unsupported cell type. Cannot start run. Problem: You tried to start a run while no cell has been installed on the instrument base or the type of cell installed is not supported by this instrument software.

Url.Title: Message 159
Url.Abstract: Message 159 Cell disconnected while method running. Run terminated. Problem: The cell lost connection while the experiment was in progress; therefore the run was stopped.

Url.Title: Status Message 213
Url.Abstract: Status Message 213 LNCS text. This is a text message from the Liquid Nitrogen Cooling System (LNCS). This message should not appear on your system. If it does, please call TA Instruments for service.

Url.Title: Message 541
Url.Abstract: Message 541 Tray missing. Cannot start method. Problem: The Autosampler tray is not present. The run cannot start without the tray of samples and sample pans.

Url.Title: Message 542
Url.Abstract: Message 542 Cannot select PCA installed while a pressure cell is mounted. The DSC pressure cell is not compatible with the Photocalorimeter Accessory and they cannot be used together. You need to remove the pressure cell and install the standard DSC cell before installing the PCA.

Url.Title: Message 543
Url.Abstract: Message 543 Pressure cell requires T1 heat flow selection. Problem: When using the DSC pressure cell you have selected a heat flow other than the required T1 type.

Url.Title: Message 544
Url.Abstract: Message 544 PCA experiments above 80°C require a non-standard quartz light guide. Most PCA experiments are run isothermally. The PCA is compatible with two Q Series DSC coolers—FACS and RCS. Generally, PCA experiments are performed in the temperature range –50 to 80°C using the standard Extended Range Liquid Light Guide provided with the unit. A quartz light guide is available as an option and must be used for experiments above 80°C. The range with the quartz light guide is –50 to 250°C.

Url.Abstract: Message 612 LNCS serial out com task exits. Problem: The LNCS has gone offline with the controller. Solution:

Url.Title: Message 613
Url.Abstract: Message 613 LNCS serial in task exits. Problem: The LNCS has gone offline with the controller. Solution:

Url.Title: Message 626
Url.Abstract: Message 626 Cell disconnected from instrument. Problem: The cell lost connection while the experiment was in progress; therefore the run was stopped.

Url.Title: Message 627
Url.Abstract: Message 627 Calibration file is for a different cooling unit. Problem: The Tzero calibration results were obtained from a cooling device different from the one currently selected.

Url.Title: Message 628
Url.Abstract: Message 628 Calibration file is for a different cell. The cell serial number contained in the data file that you have selected to analyze for calibration purposes does not match the serial number of the installed cell.

Url.Title: Message 629
Url.Abstract: Message 629 Error reading calibration file. Problem: The file that you have attempted use cannot be read.

Url.Title: Message 630
Url.Abstract: Message 630 Bad entry in calibration file. Problem: When analyzing a calibration file, the file path length for one or more of the Tzero calibration files has exceeded the instrument's character limit of 125 characters.

Url.Title: Message 631
Url.Abstract: Message 631 Too many records in calibration file. Problem: The calibration file contains too many records.

Url.Title: Message 632
Url.Abstract: Message 632 Cell not covered at method start. Run continuing. Problem: The DSC AutoLid was not closed at the beginning of the run. The run sequence will continue.

Url.Title: Message 633
Url.Abstract: Message 633 Cell memory full. Problem: You tried to enter a value that was stored in the cell and could not write to a cell because the cell memory is full.

Url.Title: Message 634
Url.Abstract: Message 634 Line frequency interrupt not detected. Method terminated. There is a problem with the system. (The instrument has stopped receiving zero cross interrupts from the PCU while a method is running.)

Url.Title: Message 635
Url.Abstract: Message 635 Tzero calibration file not loaded at method start. Run continuing. Problem: There is no Tzero calibration in effect at the start of this experiment. The experiment will continue but the results may not be as expected.

Url.Title: Message 636
Url.Abstract: Message 636 Please remove the sample pan from the cell. Press the cal button again to begin cell sample calibration.

Url.Title: Message 637
Url.Abstract: Message 637 Please remove the reference pan from the cell. Press the cal button again to begin cell reference calibration.

Url.Title: Message 638
Url.Abstract: Message 638 Cell memory read/write task exits. There is a problem with the system. Solution: Reset the instrument. If the problem persists, contact TA Instruments for service.

Url.Title: Status Message 640
Url.Abstract: Status Message 640 Autosampler sequence halted. Problem: An error has occurred to halt the Autosampler sequence.

Url.Title: Message 642
Url.Abstract: Message 642 High volume pans cannot be used to obtain Heat Flow T4P. Problem: The high volume DSC pans cannot be used to obtain heat flow T4P.

Url.Title: Message 643
Url.Abstract: Message 643 LNCS empty. Cannot start run. Problem: You have set up a run that requires the LNCS to provide liquid nitrogen cooling, but the LNCS is empty. The run will not be started until the LNCS contains adequate liquid nitrogen.

Url.Title: Message 644
Url.Abstract: Message 644 LNCS emptied. Run continuing. Problem: The LNCS has run out of liquid nitrogen in the middle of your experiment. The run will continue, but the results may not be as expected.

Url.Title: Message 645
Url.Abstract: Message 645 LNCS below autofill level at method start. Cannot start run. The LNCS has gone below the level you have specified for autofill at the start of the experiment. The run will continue.

Url.Title: Message 646
Url.Abstract: Message 646 Fatal LNCS com port error. Problem: There is no communication between the LNCS and the controller.

Url.Title: Message 647
Url.Abstract: Message 647 LNCS Overpressure. Problem: The maximum allowable pressure in the LNCS tank has been exceeded.

Url.Title: Message 648
Url.Abstract: Message 648 LNCS Cool Timeout. Problem: While cooling the LNCS must receive a "Cool" command at least once every second or it will revert to its default idle state and this error will be displayed.

Url.Title: Message 649
Url.Abstract: Message 649 LNCS Fill Complete. This is a message to inform you that the LNCS has been successfully filled. No further action is required.

Url.Title: Message 650
Url.Abstract: Message 650 LNCS Fill Terminated. Problem: The fill process has been stopped. This may be caused by one of several situations: empty bulk tank, bulk tank valve closed, no fill line connected, or full tank detected before fill set point was reached.

Url.Title: Message 668
Url.Abstract: Message 668 Cell temperature below ambient. Equilibrating to ambient temperature before opening lid.

Url.Title: Message 670
Url.Abstract: Message 670 LNCS Communication Error. Problem: A communication error has occurred. Solution: Check the connections shown in the figure to the right, reset the LNCS and repeat the operation. If the error persists, contact TA Instruments for service.

Url.Title: Message 671
Url.Abstract: Message 671 Lid enabled. Please remove the DPC before rebooting the instrument. Problem: When the instrument is reset (rebooted), the lid will automatically close. It cannot close with the Differential Photocalorimeter (DPC) in position.

Url.Title: Message 673

Url.Title: Message 727

Problem: The experiment temperature range specified for this experiment (done with the FACS cooling accessory) exceeds the Tzero calibration range. The run will continue but the results may not be as expected because the data taken outside the calibration range will be less accurate than that inside the calibration range.

Url.Title: Message 729
Url.Abstract: Message 729 T1 heat flow selected. Cannot start modulated run. Problem: The DSC cannot run Modulated DSC (MDSC) experiments when the selected heat flow is T1.

Url.Title: Message 731
Url.Abstract: Message 731 Unsupported cooler. Cannot start run. Problem: The selected cooler is not supported by this instrument.

Url.Title: Message 734
Url.Abstract: Message 734 Quench Cooling Accessory (QCA) can be used only to determine Heat Flow T1. Cannot start run.

Url.Title: Status Message 735
Url.Abstract: Status Message 735 Cooling unit selected based on calibration file. Verify before use. Problem: This message is displayed after you reset the instrument parameters using the Instrument Setup wizard. When the instrument parameters are reset, the type of cooler selected previously is lost. The cooling unit will be selected based on the current calibration file.

Url.Title: Status Message 736
Url.Abstract: Status Message 736 Heat flow results using this pan type are not optimized. Problem: The type of pan you have selected is not the best for the heat flow type.

Url.Title: Message 737
Url.Abstract: Message 737 Heat flow results using this gas are not optimized. Problem: The heat flow results that you will get using the chosen gas are not the optimum possible.

Url.Title: Message 744
Url.Abstract: Message 744 PCA requires T4 or T4P heatflow. Cannot start run. Problem: When using the Photocalorimeter Accessory (PCA) you have selected T1 heat flow.

Url.Abstract: Message 831 Pan factors updated. Sample=____ Ref=____

Url.Title: Message 835
Url.Abstract: Message 835 Autosampler manual calibration saved. This is an informational message to let you know that the Autosampler manual calibration has been successfully saved. For more information on the calibration, see the DSC online help file.

Url.Title: Message 836

Url.Title: Message 845

Url.Title: TMA Messages
Url.Abstract: TMA Messages These messages can apply to any of the TA Instruments' Thermomechanical Analyzer instruments online with the controller. Refer to the Help messages for solutions to the problems.

Url.Title: Message 120
Url.Abstract: Message 120 Zero length, measure length, or close probe failed. Check probe. Problem: The Dimension Change signal will not stabilize within a specified amount of time or no dimension change was detected.

Url.Title: Message 121
Url.Abstract: Message 121 Probe not zeroed. Cannot measure or move probe. Problem: When the system was reset or the mode selection changed, you did not zero the probe. The instrument cannot measure the sample or move the probe.

Url.Title: Message 122
Url.Abstract: Message 122 Probe travel exceeded limit. Check probe and stage. Problem: This message is caused by one of the following:

Url.Title: Message 123
Url.Abstract: Message 123 Both probe limit sensors blocked. Cannot zero, measure or move probe. Problem: A problem exists with the hardware.

Url.Title: Message 124
Url.Abstract: Message 124 Probe or force calibration time-out. Problem: The Dimension Change signal will not stabilize within a specified amount of time because an applied force value could not be determined to balance the system.

Url.Title: Message 126
Url.Abstract: Message 126 Probe or force not zeroed or calibrated. Cannot set force, measure or move probe. Problem:

Url.Title: Message 127
Url.Abstract: Message 127 Zero, measure or probe movement already in progress. Problem: You have pressed a key which requires probe movement; however, the probe is already moving as a result of a previous operation.

Url.Title: Message 128
Url.Abstract: Message 128 Calibration in progress. Cannot zero, measure or move probe. Problem: You have pressed a key which requires probe movement; however, the probe is already moving as a result of either force or probe calibration procedures in progress.

Url.Title: Message 129
Url.Abstract: Message 129 Isostrain deflection out of range. Change percent deflection. Problem: The LVDT deflection or force required for Isostrain operation is outside of the normal range.

Url.Title: Message 131

Url.Title: Message 132
Url.Abstract: Message 132 Probe not in the closed position. Run continuing. Problem: This is a warning that you left the probe up off the sample and/or that the LVDT is not in range. The run will continue, but you will not get valid readings from the probe.

Url.Title: Message 133
Url.Abstract: Message 133 Force not calibrated or calibration in progress. Cannot start run. Problem: You have tried to start a run; however, one of the following situations has occurred:

Url.Title: Message 134
Url.Abstract: Message 134 Zero, measure, or probe movement in progress. Cannot start run. Problem: You have tried to start a run while one of the operations requiring probe movement was already in progress.

Url.Title: Message 137
Url.Abstract: Message 137 Sample temperature not changing. Furnace not closed. Run terminated. Problem: The furnace was left in the up position and the run was started. Heater power is applied to the furnace, but the sample thermocouple does not register a temperature increase. The run is aborted.

Url.Title: Message 139
Url.Abstract: Message 139 Drive board failure. Cannot zero, measure, move probe or furnace. Problem: The motor drive board did not pass the Confidence test.

Url.Title: Message 140
Url.Abstract: Message 140 Size measurement out of range. Clear stage and zero length. Problem: A sample was on the stage when the Zero Length operation was last performed. This results in a false zero reading and the size measurement falls out of range.

Url.Title: Message 141
Url.Abstract: Message 141 Cannot zero length or measure length while a method is running. Problem: You have tried to start a zero length or measure length operation while the method is in progress.

Url.Title: Message 142
Url.Abstract: Message 142 Cannot air cool. Method is running or furnace is not open. Problem: You have either selected the air cool function while a method was in progress or the furnace was not in the up position as required.

Url.Title: Message 143
Url.Abstract: Message 143 Probe stuck to sample or movement is obstructed. Cannot move probe. Problem: The probe is stuck to the sample or its movement is somehow obstructed.
